Otter remains a convenient tool, but reliability has slipped. Recording from both phone and laptop has grown glitchier, and my latest 90-minute meeting has been â€œprocessingâ€ for six hours despite my paid plan. Transcription accuracy also trails other apps I use, leading to heavy editsâ€”particularly when multiple speakers have foreign accents. Useful, but increasingly frustrating.
